<br>
And, it does occasionally lock up.  That'd be my biggest complaint about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eliezeroferudin>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Order of Crimson Hands</span><br>  Posts: 1350<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/6/03 3:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1524.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: D&amp;D Character Generator</span><hr size=1> Yes, the Official Generator is horribly buggy, but it does its job:  It allows you to easily look at 'samples' of your character through various levels so you can figure out they type of character you want to play, and how his progression will look.<br>
<br>
But for really creating and maintaining your character, I say USE PEN AND PAPER.  :-p<br>
<br>
Seriously, my group is at the point that they rely on the generator so much that they do not understand the rules, the matematics behind the rules, and the logic of how and why the rules are the way they are.<br>
<br>
All three of those, by the way, I think are essential to really understanding the game, especially if you ever will DM.<br>
<br>
It is like not being able to play Solataire without Windows :-p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fauxknight>Fauxknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/9/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1524.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: D&amp;D Character Generator</span><hr size=1> Not to get into a long debate about what was to be MasterTools, but no there never was much of a good character generator out there. Personally I like doing it by pen and paper too, unless its the character has some complex numbers involved (i.e. Shadowrun) at which point I use Excel to keep track of the numbers...actually there's a fairly comprehensive Excel based character generator out there, not sure what its called, but I saw that it gets pretty complex.<br>
<br>
